    "body": "Hey @alexandraB99 @jrainville I've created some designs for this which have been signed off by @John-44 \r\n\r\nTo echo mobile, we can use the grey dot to the right of any channel that has unread messages. If the unread messages contain a mention, the grey dot would be replaced with the blue notification badge. Both should be replaced with the mute icon if the channel is muted. \r\n\r\nThe grey unread messages marker dot should only be removed when the user has read all of the messages in that channel. Not simply by clicking on the channel as we have now. The unread messages dot and the accompanying semibold treatment for the channel label would only be removed if the user either manually scrolled to the latest message in the channel or used the 'jump to' latest message button as shown in the video below:\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/110033914/218825926-4d597a30-443d-4e7d-a460-c642b5f17c74.mov\r\n\r\nThe user should also be able to right-click the channel and select `Mark as Read` - this would have the same effect as viewing all messages.\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/110033914/218831511-afe0b5cc-70c6-4d79-87bb-253c4c8f29d4.mov\r\n\r\nFigma designs:\r\nhttps://www.figma.com/file/Mr3rqxxgKJ2zMQ06UAKiWL/%F0%9F%92%AC-Chat%E2%8E%9CDesktop?node-id=21556%3A681150&t=umUsHzhThBLH3NTa-4\r\n\r\nIf whoever is developing this could set up a call with myself before implementing that would be great - just so we can chat through all of the interactions!\r\nThanks!",
